WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.400 --> 00:00:10.800
I recently had a chance to discuss wealth
confiscation with John Rubino of DollarCollapse.com.

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:15.600
He reminds us of what governments do when
under pressure; time and time again we have

00:00:15.600 --> 00:00:22.679
seen wealth confiscation. Inflation is an
easy way to steal from your population, you

00:00:23.300 --> 00:00:30.340
have taxes, laws altered to take your money,
and then as things get worse, the wealth confiscation

00:00:31.160 --> 00:00:36.070
just gets more extreme.
Citing a few examples from the Roman Empire,

00:00:36.070 --> 00:00:40.489
John also covers a few things that have happened
in U.S. history.

00:00:40.489 --> 00:00:46.530
* 1942, after entering World War II, FDR moved
all Japanese citizens living in the U.S. to

00:00:46.530 --> 00:00:52.820
concentration camps and sold off their property.
The detainees were released in 1945, given

00:00:52.820 --> 00:00:59.820
$25 and a train ticket home - without being
reimbursed for their losses.

00:01:00.090 --> 00:01:04.080
* During the U.S. Civil War, Lincoln with
the help of Congress passed laws confiscating

00:01:04.080 --> 00:01:11.080
property used for "insurrectionary purposes"
and of citizens generally engaged in rebellion.

00:01:11.360 --> 00:01:18.360
* 1933, FDR banned the private ownership of
gold, gave those who surrendered it $20.67

00:01:18.619 --> 00:01:25.229
per ounce and then devalued the dollar to
$35 an ounce, effectively stealing 70% of

00:01:25.229 --> 00:01:28.780
the wealth of those who surrendered their
gold.

00:01:28.780 --> 00:01:33.289
